  "text": "In Fig.4 we show ξ 2 (t) as a function of time for a large atom number. The curve is indeed quite flat around the best squeezing time t min . There are two solutions to equation (37): t η < t min and t ′ η > t min . When N → ∞, t η is finite and given by (53). On the other hand, as we show in Appendix A, t min diverges as N 1/4 and t ′ η diverges as N 1/2 . Knowing the asymptotic behavior of t min , by introducing appropriate rescalings of the time variable as in [CITATION_1] , it is also possible to obtain the first finite size correction to ξ 2 min . This is given in equation (A4) of Appendix A.",
